data.name: Kabutops

attacks.name: Primal Scythe
attacks.text: You may discard Helix Fossil, Dome Fossil, or Old Amber from your hand. If you do, this attack does 20 damage plus 50 more damage.

attacks.name: Rock Slide
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

data.flavorText: It is thought that this Pokémon came onto land because its prey adapted to life on land.

abilities.name: Ancient Shell
abilities.text: As long as you have Omanyte or Omastar in play, damage done to Kabutops by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Energy Stream
attacks.text: Search your discard pile for a basic Energy card and attach it to Kabutops.

attacks.name: Extra Claws
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is Pokémon-ex, this attack does 50 damage plus 30 more damage.

data.name: Kabutops

attacks.name: Absorb
attacks.text: Remove a number of damage counters from Kabutops equal to half the damage done to the Defending Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance) (rounded up to the nearest 10). If Kabutops has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them.

data.flavorText: Its sleek shape is perfect for swimming. It slashes prey with its claws and drains the body fluids.

attacks.name: Vital Drain
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is Knocked Out by this attack, remove all Special Conditions and 7 damage counters from Kabutops (all if there are less than 7).

attacks.name: Thunderous Blow
attacks.text: Does 40 damage plus 10 more damage for each Lightning Energy attached to Kabutops.

data.name: Kabutops

attacks.name: Hydrocutter
attacks.text: Flip a number of coins equal to the number of Energy cards attached to Kabutops. This attack does 40 damage times the number of heads. You can't flip more than 3 coins in this way.

data.flavorText: In the water, it tucks its limbs to become more compact, then it wiggles its shell to swim fast.

data.name: Kabutops

abilities.name: Primal Shell
abilities.text: As long as Kabutops is your Active Pokémon, your opponent can't play any Trainer cards from his or her hand.

attacks.name: Chop Up
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon that has any damage counters on it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

data.flavorText: It is thought that this Pokémon came onto land because its prey adapted to life on land.

abilities.name: Primal Aura
abilities.text: As long as Kabutops is your Active Pokémon, neither player can play Basic Pokémon or Evolution cards from his or her hand to evolve Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Dual Cut
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads.

abilities.name: Primal Stare
abilities.text: As long as Kabutops is your Active Pokémon, your opponent can't play any Basic Pokémon or Evolution cards from his or her hand to evolve his or her Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Luring Antenna
attacks.text: Before doing damage, you may choose 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon and switch it with 1 of the Defending Pokémon. If you do, this attack does 20 damage to the new Defending Pokémon. Your opponent chooses the Defending Pokémon to switch.

abilities.name: Fossilized Memories
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, your opponent can't play any Supporter cards from their hand.

attacks.name: Rock Slide
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

data.flavorText: Its body had begun to change so it could function on land. But it didn't adapt in time and went extinct.

data.name: Kabutops ex
rules: When Pokémon-ex has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Hydrocutter
attacks.text: Flip a number of coins equal to the amount of Energy attached to Kabutops ex. This attack does 40 damage times the number of heads. You can't flip more than 3 coins in this way.

attacks.name: Spiral Drain
attacks.text: Remove 2 damage counter from Kabutops ex (remove 1 if there is only 1).

data.name: Shining Kabutops
rules: You can't have more than 1 Shining Kabutops in your deck.

attacks.name: Lightning Cut
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 damage plus 10 more damage and does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) If tails, this attack does 30 damage and Shining Kabutops does 10 damage to itself.

attacks.name: Water Slash
attacks.text: Does 50 damage plus 10 more damage for each Water Energy attached to Shining Kabutops but not used to pay for this attack's Energy cost. Don't apply Resistance.

data.flavorText: This ancient Pokémon uses its razor-sharp claws to cut open its prey and gain access to its blood.

abilities.name: Crystal Type
abilities.text: Whenever you attach a Water, Lightning, or Fighting basic Energy card from your hand to Kabutops, Kabutops's type (color) becomes the same as that type of Energy until the end of the turn.

attacks.name: Draining Cut
attacks.text: Remove a damage counter from Kabutops.

attacks.name: Triple Cutter
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

data.name: Kabutops

abilities.name: Ancient Way
abilities.text: Apply Weakness for your opponent's Active Pokémon as ×4 instead.

attacks.name: Draining Blade
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: The cause behind the extinction of this species is unknown. Kabutops were aggressive Pokémon that inhabited warm seas.
